description:
The portmanteau chaordic refers to a system of governance that blends characteristics of chaos and order.

The mix of chaos and order is often described as a harmonious coexistence displaying characteristics of both, with neither chaotic nor ordered behavior dominating. Some hold that nature is largely organized in such a manner; in particular, living organisms and the evolutionary process by which they arose are often described as chaordic in nature. The chaordic principles have also been used as guidelines for creating human organizations that would be neither centralized nor anarchical networks.

Mathias Schaffhäuser Artist Bio:

Mathias Schaffhäuser has been on the techno, house and minimal scene since 1994 when his first House EP was released on Definitive Records. 25 years later he is still at. 
In the first quarter of 2021, he already was part of 2 cool remix projects, one for Si Begg's impressive remix series „Peripheral Original Motion Picture Soundtrack: Remixed“, and one for Öona Dahl and Hallucienda Records. 

In 2020, Mathias' label WARE released its catalogue number 100. To celebrate this anniversary Mathias released the EP "A Hundred Acts Of Devotion" with 5 new tracks. October 2020 saw the release of „On The Brink, Vol. 1“, the first remix EP of FANATICO's 2nd album, featuring Man Power, Amir Alexander, Warehouse Preservation Society, Indoor Man and Ulysses on remix duty.

2019 saw the sophomore release from his Fanatico project 'Love And Dancing On The Brink' on Hallucienda in November (vinyl and CD in January 2020), as well as the September release of his new album 'Hedonism, What Else' on Snork Enterprises, new EPs on Fenou, Biotop Label and Ware Records, and several remixes. 

In 2018 there was already a reason to celebrate: The 20th jubilee of WARE was honoured with 3 releases featuring reworked and remixed Ware classics like „Nice To Meet You“ and „Desire“. Also 3 more EPs on Tiefschwarz' Souvenir Music, legendary British label Third Ear, and Biotop Label came out in 2018.

Other releases from Mathias have appeared on Mo's Ferry Productions, Compost, Tic Tac Toe Rec., Kompakt, Force Inc., Multicolor, BluFin Records, Adjunct, WIR Recordings, Blaou Sounds and many others. In 1997 he started WARE, releasing 99 EPs as of April 2019. His album Lido Hotel with the well known track Nice To Meet You, released in 2000, marked his breakthrough in the techno scene. 2001 saw his massive club hit Hey Little Girl, and in 2002 Musik ohne Bass permeated the clubs. In April 2005 he released his album Coincidance, its title track successfully remixed by Trentemøller. On his album Unequal Equality (2009) Mathias collaborated with Lucy, Alex Smoke, Xhin, And.id, Benjamin Brunn and many others. He also produced remixes for Steve Bug (LoverBoy), Luomo (Tessio), Faust, [A]pendics.Shuffle, Goldfrapp, Pan-Pot, Indoor Life, Northern Lite, Dapayk & Padberg – to name a few.

As DJ, Schaffhäuser’s motto at the turntables is: “Purism sucks!” The quality of the music is what’s important, not sheer functionality and trendiness. At times his sets can be rather varied from his very own style, dirty + dark house, and thumping techno. More and more Mathias uses his microphone and croons to his records, creating a very special live experience (https://soundcloud.com/mathias-schaffhauser/sets/mixes).

Bio:
A serious career in producing electronic music almost always starts in a club: everyone knows the story of his first night out at some legendary place, sometimes behind the turntables, more often than not in front of them. Everybody remembers how this sound hit him for the first time, how the doors to the paradise of the steady bassdrum opened. The hero of our story found its initiation at Aufschwung Ost, famous predecessor to the fabulous Stammheim Kassel, which may be defunct but still resides as referential limbo in the hearts of many. However, music hasn't been a stranger for the then 16 years old Martin: already the first portable radio was manipulated for the first steps towards sampling, the belt-driven turntables were scratched to death and the amiga 500 gobbed primal hip hop beats. Although nothing of this sounded like Public Enemy or A Tribe Called Quest it still sufficed to make the young apprentice's mouth water. Then Techno came along with its massive impact, followed by the first shaky dj gig in front of a real crowd at Aufschwung Ost, the first Akai sampler, the first Atari computer, the first field recording, the first loops on 123 BPM, finally the movement to Cologne, being a techno stronghold back then. It's a near classic biography for Martin Beume who has grown to become one respected producer and DJ, but without the attitude. He prefers to stay in the background and lets the music take the center stage. But he who inhales the groove has to exhale at some point too, so Martin's first demo tracks landed at Sub Static, where he released two EP's under his monicker Golden Red. Both featured chopped up funk with a warm-hearted flavour and rank amongst the classics of the label. With Pawas, Martin found a kindred spirit to produce some great tracks for Adam Kroll's Squonk outlet or the people at Brut. That's also the point where Martin found the guts to embark on a solo career under his civic name, which has been a wise decision as the first 12“ on Outils Du Connaisseur arrestingly shows.

I was born in Ufa, Russia. At 12 years old I moved to England where I started playing drums. Then at 15 I picked up the guitar and despite being completely tone deaf I started strumming and singing songs by bands like Blink182, Greenday and The Red Hot Chili Peppers. After taking some singing lessons, I decided to explore it seriously at the age of 16-18, also the age when I took Music Technology courses and learnt how to record music. 
After finishing school, music was the only thing that I wanted to do. I went to the University of Westminster to study Commercial Music. All I did was sit in the studio for 3 years and smoked lots of stuff. Listening back to some of my work from that time there is a clear pattern. First year of university: the work is shabby/simple/no attention to details. Second year: getting better, need more attention to details and to improve as a musician. Third year, getting decent though songs take far longer to make now than they did in the first year :-). 
After finishing University I decided to take a chance and moved to Vancouver, Canada to get my citizenship there. That's where I started my first real band 'Alma Nine'. It took a while but we were pretty good at covers and our own stuff, but gigs were hard to get until we finally recorded our album 'Time Changes All'. After that things started to fall into place a little, but our drummer had to move back to his native Germany. 
So the band broke up and decided to go solo for now, until I move to LA next september. 
This is music that has been in me from the start but I never sat down and recorded it. If you are reading this, listen to the music in good headphones, pretty loudly and please give it 100% of your attention as there is a lot of stuff going on. 
Thanks!

BIO
The Concise characteristics of Ryan Davis's music are within the inexhaustible dimensions of sound, taking the listener on a journey full of stories which describe dreams, desires and create imaginary worlds within oneself. 

Since 2006 you can follow Ryan's traces on almost every important melodic electronic music label worldwide such as Erased Tapes, Anjunadeep, Watergate, Traumschallplatten, Bedrock, Last Night on Earth or Klangwelt Records. Touring the planet constantly inspires Ryan´s musical aesthetics whose quality brought him an international fan base and a reputation that is nothing short of remarkable. 

Over the years he collected notable attention by a variety of artists out of  every electronic music genre such as Aphex Twin, Olafur Arnalds, Stephan Bodzin, Apparat, Max Cooper, Sasha, Vessels, Boys Noise or even Depeche Mode including his music on their ‘Sound of the Universe‘ tour. As well he is playing all around the globe being invited to iconic venues like Bilbaos Guggenheim Museum or Berlin´s legendary Funkhaus.

Nowadays Ryan represents a fundamental name in the modern electronic music culture, in which compositional qualities are a must. His remixes for masterminds like Olafur Arnalds and Nils Frahm, collaborations with Robot Koch or Alex Banks underline his work and musical mindset to celebrate & spread the compositional form of electronic music which leads the way to establish a world on its own besides pure dj-functionality.

On a quest for the ultimate unifying experience... the moment of absolute presence… 

Chris Liebing’s friendly demeanour and beaming smile make him enormously recognisable in the modern electronic music landscape, but it’s the years of passionate dedication to his craft as an artist that have made him synonymous with Techno. 

A pioneer of the European contribution to the story of Techno, the Giessen (Germany) born producer and DJ has been active the world over since the 1990s and, at every stage of his career, has helped create a platform for other artists, not to mention the scene in general to flourish. Whether via his long-running CLR imprint, affiliated podcast and club nights, his current radio show AM/FM or his 2020 Alone Together streams and DJs & Beers ‘talk show’, Liebing the curator extends way beyond his DJ sets. 

Since 2018’s ‘Burn Slow’ LP on Mute, Liebing’s musical direction has grown to encompass some of his earliest influences. Taking in nascent 80’s electronica, psychedelic melodies and an unmistaken seam of alternative music of the past 40 years, ‘Burn Slow’ and remixes for Depeche Mode and Goldfrapp heralded a new chapter for Liebing that continues in 2021 with the arrival of his ‘Another Day’ LP. 

Although now incorporating a wider range of sounds into his work and performances, Liebing has no interest in leaving darkened rooms and dancefloors behind and, with the return of CLR in 2021, we can look forward to more of his unmistakable presence pushing Techno forward for years to come.

Группа «Каспий» родилась в конце 2012 года, в Москве, когда музыкант Владимир Астапчик собрал вокруг себя группу музыкантов-единомышленников. Уже через полгода, летом 2013 года команда, названная «Каспий», дебютировала на фестивалях «Нашествие» и «Доброфест». Мелодичность, драйв и многослойная лирика текстов помогли группе стремительно завоевать Интернет- и офф-лайн аудиторию.
            Уже в январе 2014 группа «Каспий» стала «Открытием года» в iTunes со своим первым EP-альбомом «Расстояния», и весь 2014 год группа собирала лавры на волне этого релиза. Одноименный заглавный трек принес команде победу еще в нескольких конкурсах: «Телеком Хит» от МТС, «Aurum Inutile» на Радио России и конкурсе "Интернационал с Алёной Апиной" на радио Комсомольская Правда.
            Сингл «Расстояния» попал в ротацию «Русского Радио» (программа «Неформат»), звучал в эфире радио «Комсомольская Правда» и Love Radio, вошел в сборник «Навигация».
            Все песни с EP-альбома «Расстояния» звучат в сериале «Окрыленные» канала «Ю», трек «Имена» попал в эфир Нашего радио, Радио КП и Love Radio и вошел в виниловый сборник «ЧеStars”.
            2014 год стал для группы «Каспий» урожайным на фестивали: команда отыграла на международных фестивалях «Park Live» и «Нашествие» (Москва), «V-Pox» (Владивосток), приняла участие в столичном спортивно-музыкальном фестивале ProСпорт, акциях «Ночь живых музыкантов» и «День винила».
            Начало 2015 года команда отметила выступлением на екатеринбургском фестивале «Старый Новый Рок», после чего группа стала участником телевизионного конкурса «Главная сцена». Несмотря на плотный съемочный график из-за участия в теле-проекте, команда успела принять участие в фестивалях "Emporio Music Fest", "Благо-Фест 2015" и «Дикая Мята», а также порадовать слушателей вторым EP-альбомом «Новая жизнь». Одноименный трек со второго EP звучит в фильме Анны Меликян «Про любовь», который стал победителем международного кинофестиваля « Кинотавр 2015».
            В 2016 года музыканты представили слушателям свой свежий ЕР «Твой праздник», сняли клип на песню «Расстояния» и начали запись полноценного альбома.

Eduardo González  aka TNAO started in the world of music  at the age of 10, when he began matching disco and industrial vinyl’s that belong to one of his uncles, this impulse him for the liking and passion for the  music.
    
    When he listened track's and dj set's from producers like Gayle San, Green Velvet, Adam Beyer, Surgeon, Laurent Garnier, Dj Rolando, Plastikman, Monica Kruze, Christian Smith, Marco Carola, Chris Liebieng, among others, thanks to a good friend his taste for techno music began.
    
    7 years ago he started his career as a Dj playing and mixing genres such as Deep House, Minimal House, Filtered House and Tech House, as a consequence of his liking for Disco Music which represents great part of his musical influence.
    
    Producing since 9 years ago in an empirical way, his creation begins with techno rhythms (135 & 140 bpms) within a hard techno tendency that was invading his life between the years 1999 and 2000; he managed to meet different software and hardware’s and other ways to create music in an analogous and digital way.
    
    In 2004 began a new era of rhythms, proposing basic structures based in minimal techno, the melodic depth and the new sounds built in a digital way.
    In 2008 he built up his minimal tendency with his firsts releases in Europe and this year begins with more challenges in his career as a producer with musical and melodic arrangements based in Dub, Ambient, Tech house, House, Funk, Latin Jazz and Jazz, with changing structures focused in an progressive way to offer different atmospheres in a  same track. 
    
    His work had traveled to countries like Spain, Italy, France, winnig the respect of producers like Florian Meindi, Someone Else, Minicoolboyz, Ahmet Sendil, Autistic, Francesco Passatino, Yappac; Marco Dass, Signal Deluxe.
    Tnao had shared stage with important personalities of the world’s electronic scene like Lucient Fort, Yappac, Jacek Sienkiewicz, Santos Resiak, Signal Deluxe and Alberto Santizzo.
  
Biografía

Eduardo González aka Tnao iniciando en la música a los 10 años intentando empatar vinyles de música disco e industrial de un tío suyo, lo cual lo impulsó a tener el gusto y la pasión por la música bailable.

Comienza su gusto por el techno gracias a un gran amigo por el cuál conoció y escucho set's y tracks de dj y productores como: Gayle San, Green Velvet, Adam Beyer, Surgeon, Laurent Garnier, Dj Rolando, Plastikman, Monica Kruze, Christian Smith, Marco Carola, Chris Liebieng, entre otros. Inicio hace 7 años como dj mezclando géneros como Deep House, Minimal House, Filtered House y Tech house, generos consecuencia de su heredada afición por la música Disco, la cual representa gran parte de su influencia.

Produciendo desde hace 9 años de manera empírica, comienza su creación con ritmos de techno con bpms de 135 y 140 con la tendencia hard techno que invadía su vida en los años 1999 y 2000; logra conocer los diferentes softwares, hardwares y maneras de crear música tanto digital cómo análogamente; en el 2004 comienza una nueva era de ritmos, proponiendo estructuras basadas por el minimal techno, la profundidad de las melodías y los nuevos sonidos construidos de manera digital; en el 2008 asienta su tendencia minimal con sus primeros releases en Europa y en este 2009 comienza más retos en su carrera como productor, intentado matizar con arreglos musicales y melódicos basados en el dub, ambient, tech house, house, funk, latin jazz y jazz, con estructuras cambiantes de manera progresiva para brindar varias atmósferas en el mismo track.

Su trabajo ha podido llegar a países de Europa como España, Italia, Francia ganándose el respeto de productores como Florian Meindl, Someone Else, Minicoolboyz, Ahmet Sendil, Autistic, Francesco Passatino, Yappacc, Marco Dassi, Signal Deluxe entre otros.

Ha compartido escenarios con importantes personalidades de la escena electrónica mundial como Lucient Fort, Yapacc, Jacek Sienkiewicz, Santos Resiak, Signal Deluxe, Alberto Santizzo.

Dash Klusterz est un duo de djs/producteurs bayonnais formé en 2008.

Ils définissent eux-mêmes leurs créations studio comme une électro teintée d'italodisco, de house, de hiphop, de funk... et de toutes leurs influences acquises individuellement durant plus d'une décennie derrière les platines. Beats lourds, rythmiques galopantes, lignes de basses ravageuses et mélodies de synthés old school... tels sont les ingrédients de leurs expérimentations sonores. La diversité des styles de leurs compositions montre encore une fois leur ouverture aux différents courants de la musique électronique actuelle.
Fin 2010, avec Samuel Dougados et Aurélien « Delwood », respectivement artiste plasticien et peintre, ils seront récompensés du Prix de l’originalité par le jury du Festival des « Rencontres Improbables 5 » pour leur prestation Live au Conservatoire de Musique de Bayonne.
Leurs djsets sont, quant à eux, orientés plutôt "dancefloor" et toujours agrémentés de quelques surprises... Après plusieurs sorties sur le label Australien "RuNT Records" ainsi que sur le label parisien "StillMuzik", ils commencent à écumer les clubs et scènes français (Batofar à Paris, Heretic Club à Bordeaux, « Elektrotasuna 4» à Hasparren, « Festilasai » et Atabal à Biarritz, La Rochelle, Bourges, Toulouse, Seignosse, Pau…) mais aussi européens (Pologne, Lettonie, Espagne...) où ils jouent aux cotés de Jess & Crabe, The Toxic Avenger, Les Petits Pilous, South Central, Pro7, Dilemn, Mondkopf, Humanleft, Fulgeance, Elisa Do Brasil, La Fine Equipe, Hoosky, Tuff Wheelz, Papy Harders, Parker & Lewis…

Membres depuis 2011 de la Dirty South Family, un collectif sévissant sur les dancefloors du Sud Ouest de la France, ils lancent récemment un nouveau projet avec Clicknuts, "The Weirds", un trio live-machines electro… A suivre !!

LoYoTo are Cle & Eva Be, both original Berlin Djs since the early 90s,
deeply rooted in the music scene of the city. Though both each have a long lasting career of their own, their energetic and diverse back2back DJ sets are still some kind of a well kept secret
********************************************************************
LoYoTo are the east-berlin born Eva Be and Cle from the western part of the formerly divided city. Both started their dj and producer career almost at the same time at the core of the then developing scene in the very center of Berlin, just after the wall came down.

originally rooted in very different styles of music, they encountered for the first time djing together in 2012,finding common ground in more than just music – a gig, that should lead to more: They decided to combine their talents and knowledge and build a studio together.
here, and during legendary back2back dj sets, they finally united their different musical backgrounds – dub/reggae and underground house music and defined their very own sound – the first result being their release „looking at the starz“ ep on upon you records. after a bunch of remixes, they released the second ep "lonely young tourist" on watergate records. “karmadog” & "buchin ep" on foul & sunk. in 2019, the two impulsive musicians decided to create their own recordlabel. "LYT Recordings is a publishing platform for music in the shades and between the bars." 
her highly acclaimed ambient album "Sicker Man Variations" was released here in collaboration with multi-instrumentalist Sicker Man. the second release is an absolute dub bomb and a hearty ep. 
n addition, they refined with their sound remixes for Fat Freddy's Drop, Donna Summer, Clara Hill, and many more.

DJ and producer Justin Faust has been a well-known part of the international dance music scene for more than ten years. Based in Munich, but closely associated with the Portuguese DISCOTEXAS label (Moullinex, Xinobi and others) and New York’s legendary Nervous Records, his style is as diverse as the people he works with, having releases and remixes show influences from Nu Disco, House, Funk and beyond. Apart from numerous original releases like his 2014 album “Spellbound”, he has crafted many popular remixes for the likes of Childish Gambino, Treasure Fingers, Goldroom, Moullinex or The Knocks, not to be outdone by classic earlier reworks of Missy Elliot, Justin Timberlake, Daft Punk, Ariana Grande and Janet. What followed were extensive DJ gigs and tours as headliner, playing at parties across Europe, the US, South America and Asia as well as appearances on Annie Mac's BBC1 radio show, a feature in the critically acclaimed TV show "The Leftovers" and collaborations with legends like Mats Bjorklund, who has recorded with Boney M. and Giorgio Moroder.

Flex Blur est un artiste français qui, depuis une quinzaine d’années, s’amuse à explorer une multitude de styles. Influencé par la musique de jeux vidéo, puis par la scène IDM proéminente de l'époque (Aphex Twin, Squarepusher, Autechre), il a commencé la musique électronique sur PlayStation avec Music 2000 avant de composer sur ordinateur. Multi-instrumentiste en parallèle, il se donne pour objectif de mélanger les univers et de délivrer une musique pointue, afin de proposer à chaque nouvel album une immersion dans un monde bien distinct des précédents.

EN:
Flex Blur is a French artist who has been exploring several styles over the past 15 years. Taking his influences from video game music to the prominent IDM scene at the time (Aphex Twin, Squarepusher, Autechre), he started composing electronic music on PlayStation with Music 2000 before moving onto PC, while also practicing various instruments. According to him, each new album must be a full immersion in a world that is very distinct from his previous ones, as he aims to blend different universes and create unique productions.

Bookings: DNAbookings@mail.com WHAT THE HELL?! ...a phrase that DJ, producer and party-starter, DeDeDee hears all too often on account of his unique name, which by the way is pronounced Deh-Deh-Dee! Don't worry, once you hear this dancefloor damager's brand of twisted future funk you'll realise that monikers, like genres, don't really matter. And it's for exactly these reasons that DeDeDee's debut EP on New York label, System Recordings was christened, 'What The Hell?!'. Tongue-twisting as the name may be, it hasn’t stopped word spreading across the dance music underground. Respected site DogsOnAcid.com could only come close to fully describing his sound, summing it up as, "big bright party disco electro funk." Whilst über cool German outfit What! What! Records signed second release, 'Badman' to the official CD soundtrack of worldwide graffiti fest, 'Secret Wars'. Whether in the studio or DJ booth, 'Dee knows how to whip a crowd into frenzy, dropping more styles than Mr. Miyagi! In generale, il Teatrofficina Refugio funziona così: l'intero incasso delle serate-evento, come il Tiro all'artista o il Bubbocine, va al teatro stesso per le spese da affrontare (palco, gradoni per il pubblico, luci, ecc.); l'incasso delle altre serate (spettacoli, concerti, ecc. ) è diviso in parti uguali tra il teatro e l'artista che si esibisce. Il biglietto è a un prezzo abbordabile e oscilla tra i 3 e i 5 euro, a seconda della serata. Tutti quelli che portano avanti il teatro, dal punto di vista pratico e organizzativo, lo fanno gratuitamente, perché credono in questo tipo di progetto, nell’esigenza di spazi artistici liberi e autogestiti. Bisogna infatti ricordare che il senso di questo teatro, prima ancora che artistico, è politico e sociale, proprio perché è un posto occupato (due ragazzi dell’Officina sociale sono stati denunciati per questo) autorganizzato. D’altronde a Livorno non ci sono spazi a sufficienza per chi vuole provare, esibirsi, creare. Forse è azzardato investire soldi e energie in un posto che rischia di essere sgomberato perché al centro di una zona, come il quartiere Venezia, fulcro di speculazioni edilizie cittadine, ma è giusto farlo, è un segnale che la città non può e non deve ignorare. In questi mesi il pubblico è stato davvero variegato e si è visto di tutto, non solo giovani, ma anche famiglie, bambini, anziani, e questo fa ben sperare in un coinvolgimento cittadino. Se il posto funziona, se è in grado di proporre eventi e spettacoli seguiti ogni volta da decine di persone (ché così finora è stato), allora è un segnale forte per la città e le istituzioni cittadine. Un’altra importante cosa da dire è che il teatro è aperto all’esterno, chi vuole partecipare è il benvenuto, sia che voglia dare una mano nell'organizzazione, sia che voglia esibirsi come artista. A questo proposito, c’è solo una limitazione di ordine pratico, i concerti possono essere solo acustici per accordi preesistenti con coinquilini e vicinato, quindi niente gruppi "molto rumorosi", a meno che non organizzino i loro concerti in modalità acustica (senza amplificazione o con amplificazione minima – che potrebbe essere anche uno stimolo creativo). Quindi, chiunque voglia partecipare ai lavori del teatro, alla programmazione, alle riunioni, agli eventi può presentarsi direttamente al teatro sugli Scali del Refugio.8 - Livorno.

Wandering Stylus is the new alter ego of London rave veteran Luke Kelly. With a DJ career spanning several genres, a range of different identities and 3 continents, the Wandering Stylus project was a natural progression for Luke as he continues his global adventures. Having lived 'location independent' for the last few years moving around South America, Asia and Europe, the aim with Wandering Stylus is to capture and share some of those experiences through house and techno music. 

Before the wandering began... 
Luke has played all over the UK and Europe in front of crowds of up to 3000 people at venues like; Brixton Academy, Camden Palace (now Koko), Bagleys, Egg, SeOne/The Drome, Heaven, Birmingham NEC, Ministry of Sound, The Coronet, The Sanctuary, AIR, Alexandra Palace, Melkveg (Amsterdam, Holland), Collosus (Llorett de Mar, Spain). There have also been numerous secret warehouse appearances as well as some exciting times at festivals like Bug Jam and Dance Island.

A 10 year residency with Raindance, the UK’s oldest legal rave promotion - has taken Luke up and down the UK and across Europe. As Lukozade he‘s played for all the major players in the rave scene in England, names like; Moondance, Slammin’ Vinyl, Hardcore Heaven, Innovation, Helter Skelter, HTID, Dreamscape. With his house and techno hat on, Luke has featured on the same lineup as DJ’s such as Eric Morillo, Chris Lake, Bodyrox, Funkagenda and Gordon Edge whilst also featuring regularly at ‘secret’ warehouse parties all over East London for parties like Deep Down.

Textbeak has been making and DJing dark and unusual music for many years now. Influenced by artists like Coil, Cabaret Voltaire, and Skinny Puppy, in the late 80s he began making music with whatever he had on hand in projects with long time friend Todd Sines (Planet E, Peacefrog). In 1991 Mike moved to Columbus, Ohio with Todd and joined up with Titonton Duvante (Residual Records) and Charles Noel aka Archetype (Ongaku, Black Nation) to start B/Re (Body Release). In 1994, his band Bath signed with Jevan Records (owned by gothic band Lestat) and recorded at Noise with producer Kramer (Shimmy Disc, Bongwater, Low, Galaxie 500). In 1998 he began to release solo works as Textbeak on labels such as Dark Daze (Carlos Peron of Yello), Moon Sounds (Dallas), Lasergun (Savas Pascalidis in Berlin), Tundra Dubs (Worker/Parasite), Sequel Sound (San Francisco). His label Philtre Com (with Claus Muzak Lucas Kuzma) released works by NT89 and others. In 2011 he began TXTBK's CHVяCH XV BяXK3N 7ANGvAG Radio which has become a staple of the dark electronic scene and featured mixes by Philipp Strobel [aufnahme + wiedergabe], CRIM3S, BLVCK CEILING, Clan Destine Records, Mannequin Records and many others. He has done many DJ mixes including Grim Harvest Halloween 2012 for Мишка with actor Omar Doom (Quentin Tarantino's Inglorious Basterds), Cleopatra Records and THE BRVTALIST. He has performed at events opening for Merzbow, Modern English, Bestial Mouths, Larry Tee, Nitzer Ebb, David J (of Bauhaus), Light Asylum, Test Department, Skin Town (Nick Turco of Zola Jesus), Meat Beat Manifesto, and The Legendary Pink Dots to name a few. He has remixed many artists including Blush Response (Ant-Zen), Architect (Daniel Myer of Haujobb), Tamara Sky (Lil Death LA), Bestial Mouths (Cleopatra, Clan Destine), and ∆AIMON (Tundra/Artoffact). From his compositions to his genre-destroying DJ sets, he constantly creates new and unusual sound collages and mixes. His latest release, Sick For Songs A Season Eats is on Cleopatra Records with a remix album coming out very soon.

Gordon has been involved with the music industry for 25+ years. With a hugely successful background in studio and broadcast production his name first became synonymous with the early Indie movement where he produced/engineered records for bands such as The BMX Bandits, The Vaselines and The Soup Dragons. He subsequently went on to record several Gold & Platinum award winning studio albums with International artists, recorded hundreds of sessions (including Paul Weller, Joan Baez, Tori Amos and Alanis Morrisette) and won several NY Radio Festival awards for radio sessions and In-Concert series he produced.

After first using the internet in the early nineties, Gordon identified it's massive potential for music distribution and was soon dragged screaming and kicking away from his main love of recording to spend the next 10 years pioneering in this field. This time was spent, advising clients such as George Michael, Virgin Radio and Aim (Association of Independent Music) on digital music delivery. More recently Gordon was co-founder of Broad Street Digital where he spent most of the last 18 months in the US developing systems to handle digital distribution for 800+ record labels worldwide, including V2 Records and Skint.

Earlier this year Gordon left Broad Street Digital to concentrate on a new music business venture called Major-G that will see him return to his first love of music production and management.

They didn't start the riot? Maybe they did. Bringing some fresh air to Vienna's club scene DJ/producer/promoter duo Pola-Riot has established one of the most unique club nights in Austria's capital. The guys are known for their explosive sets, blending electro, future techno and house, destined to make crowds freak out big time. They played numerous national and international festivals and venues in recent years, for instance Austria's main open air Frequency and Urban Art Forms, the country's biggest festival for electronic music. 
Pola-Riot's body of work contains commissioned remixes for fellow countrymen like Amadeus Award winners Bunny Lake or Beta Bow (of "Second Streets Have No Name", which they later re-remixed with The Bloody Beetroots for their first album) as well as for artists like Dim Mak's Mustard Pimp. Their bootleg of Stardust's French house evergreen "Music Sounds Better With You" reached the No. 1 position on the HypeM charts. Pola-Riot's track "Superpimpin" got consecutive airplay on Kissy Sell Out's BBC Radio 1 show, which earned them a signing on Tommie Sunshine's imprint Brooklyn Fire. Jack Fox from Ireland’s national broadcaster RTÉ selected the track as the "No. 1 Tune Of The Year". Their collaboration with Beta Bow, the pop-driven indie-dance tune "Rubicon" spent a month in the charts of Radio FM4, Austria's main indie radio station, and was featured on the compilation FM4 Sound Selection 31.

Electro Soul. That's what he calls it. “No one else can tell me what it sounds like!” laughs the man behind Bishop & Mulholland- Paul Dirks. For over two and half years, he has been laboring in his home studio late at night crafting a collection of songs that is both danceable and thought-provoking. “Essays and Ear Candy” is rife with glue-to-your-memory synth melodies, fervent vocals and imaginative lyricism.

Listeners often complain of deja-vu or of memory-induced song replay due to the big, (and sometimes cheezy) lead lines populating the album. “I can't get your songs out of my head!” has often been heard by his fans/sufferers. It's no surprise to discover Technotronic, Dance Mix '92 and KLF are cited as early influences on Bishop & Mulholland's electro soul sound.

While the synthesized backing and sounds give a strong digital feel to the album, it's perhaps the vocals that make Bishop & Mulholland difficult to pin down. While many of his electronic contemporaries are exploring new articulations of New Wave or Punk, Paul reaches back further, finding inspiration in the Motown sounds of Marvin Gaye, The Temptations and his favorite: the Four Tops.

And then there's the lyrics. If it were mostly dancefloor, lipstick and fast cars, you could just throw it into the “Electro” bin beside Chromeo and be done with it. But instead it's literature and vows and retribution and war-time courage. Double entendres, clever wordplays and quick rhymes are more norm than exception and approach a level of word-smithing usually associated with the brightest hiphop lyricists.

The end result sounds like Michael Jackson... and Technotronic... and Massive Attack...or maybe, like electro soul.

A theory can be "normative (or prescriptive)", meaning a postulation about what ought to be. It provides "goals, norms, and standards"

A theory is a contemplative and rational type of music.

Gizeh Records is an independent label based in Manchester, UK. Founded by Richard Knox in Leeds, 2004 and focusing on a fiercely DIY ethic, Gizeh has grown with it's artists over the years to form a strong community of musicians and artists from around the world, most of them collaborating together over the years across various projects, helping the label and those involved progress and evolve in an organic, inspiring and galvanising way.

It is our aim to conduct ourselves with modesty and humility in an ever changing industry. We put love, care and passion into our records and our artists and continue to push our ideals and our collective as far as we can within the means that we have. We have no care for genres or pigeon-holes - simply the noise of harmony and the harmony of noise and the inspiration and spirit of the people who are making that noise.
